<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF107-936-492  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 936 492  OV: 07 936 478.andO; </DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Dec 4 1989 v11 n49 p65(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Actor 1.2. (Software Review) (one of four evaluations in'Computer-aided software engineering') (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Pavlac, Ross.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Actor 1.2 from The Whitewater Group Inc rates highest of the fourCASE packages for its reasonable price, good design and includedutilities.andP;  Actor, $495, uses language that begins withobject-oriented concepts.andP;  The language is similar to C andPascal, but object-oriented programming (OOP) is integral to it.andO;Actor can run programs in its own language, C, Pascal or modulesof any Microsoft Windows-compatible languages through dynamic-linklibraries.andP;  Actor is a well-priced introduction to OOP and itshigh-level applications.andP;  There are drawbacks to Actor: itrequires learning the Actor language, which is not easy; it isunsuitable for low-level programming; and because it is aninterpreter, it is slower than packages that compile programminglanguages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Whitewater Group Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Actor 1.2 (Program development software).andO;Topic:     Computer-Aided Software EngineeringSoftware PackagesEvaluation.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   Product summary. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>